summary: If you have no idea who the hell Captain Marvel is, here’s a few quick notes: Carol Danvers was a pilot in the US Air Force....
body:
If you have no idea who the hell Captain Marvel is, here’s a few quick notes:

Carol Danvers was a pilot in the US Air Force.

Carol did a thing (the details will likely change in the movie, so whatever) that caused her to get the superpowers similar to those of an alien Kree soldier named Mar-Vell.

After getting those powers, Carol spent years as a superhero named Ms. Marvel.

You might remember Carol/Ms. Marvel as the woman that Rogue (from the X-Men) absorbed her super strength and flying powers from.

Several people have taken on the name Captain Marvel over the years, including Mar-Vell, Mar-Vell’s children, and another human named Monica Rambeau. Carol is the current Captain Marvel in the comics.

The current Ms. Marvel, a teenager from New Jersey named Kamala Khan, is one of Carol’s biggest fans.

DC Comics also has a Captain Marvel. He’s the star of the upcoming Shazam movie. DC’s Captain Marvel was made first, but Marvel Comics did a wacky legal thing that means DC can’t use that name in the title of his movie or comic books.
